TITLE: A Public Health Perspective on Menstrual Health
IDEAS IN ACTION GEN EDS: FC-POWER
COURSE DESCRIPTION
Half of the worlds population (3.9 billion people) menstruate for more than half their lives. In many societies across the world, menstruation is still an
invisible topic, surrounded by shame and secrecy. Yet weve also seen notable advocacy, education, and policy changes in the last several decades. Menstrual
Health and Hygiene (MHH) is also a human rights issue. This course will provide students an opportunity to think critically about menstrual health
scientific evidence, interventions, and advocacy.
